ope's captain in the 2008 Ryder Cup?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name was given to the fossils, discovered in 2004, of humans with large feet, that stood about a metre high?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was married to Whitney Houston from 1992 to 2007?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich singer made the news in September 2009 when Muslim groups protested that her first concert in Malaysia should be cancelled for a second time?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere is the giant copper statue of a man, woman and child, known as the African Renaissance monument, that was unveiled in April 2010?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which country launched the space station \"\"Skylab\"\" in 1973?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the occupation of St Peter, the leader of the Apostles?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the name of Canada's first woman Prime Minister?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich British stage director won an Oscar for his feature-film directing debut, which starred Kevin Spacey, Annette Bening, and Thora Birch?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Webb Ellis Cup is presented to the winners of the World Cup in what sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe borders of which European country, that were set under the reign of Afonso III (1248 to 1279), are the same today?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the five horizontal lines on and between which musical notes are written?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich half of a comedy duo was born in Lancashire in 1895?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the song \"\"The Twelve Days of Christmas\"\", what were there five of?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich art movement, founded in a Zurich caf during World War I and consolidated at a meeting held in Paris in 1920, was led by Tristan Tzara?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere was the final of the 1999 Rugby World Cup held?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name is given to notes of the same pitch, in modern tuning but written differently, such as Db / C# and Gb / F#?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which Scottish singer had hits with \"\"Maggie Mae\"\", \"\"Tonight's The Night\"\" and \"\"Do You Think I'm Sexy\"\", and has then turned to singing older standards?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"\"\"84 Charing Cross Road\"\" is a book based on 20 years of correspondence between which New York writer and Frank Doel, an antiquarian bookseller in London?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nRapidly boiling a liquid to make it thicker and more concentrated is called what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe naval base Pearl Harbour is in which US state?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In a famous speech by Winston Churchill on 4 June 1940 that began \"\"We shall fight in France, we shall fight on the seas and oceans\"\", he went on to say that \"\"we shall fight\"\" in the air, on the beaches, on the landing grounds, in the fields, in the streets, and where else?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nRunner Caster Semenya, the subject of extensive press coverage after gender testing following her win in the women's 800m at Berlin in August 2009, was from which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho won the most of the first ten tournaments called the Women's Hockey World Cup (the field hockey World Cup competition for women), which was inaugurated in 1974?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich English electronic dance music duo was made up of Neil Tennant and Chris Lowe?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat large flightless bird found in Mauritius by the Portuguese is believed to have died out in 1681?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nGabriel Loire, Mordecai Ardon and Marcelle Ferron are known for their art work in what medium?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho succeeded Prince Rainier of Monaco?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat sport is the concern of the PGA?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nDsseldorf is a major city in which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Dardanelles and the Bosporus, straits which separate Europe from the mainland of Asia, run through which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which American legal TV drama-comedy (2004 to 2008), a spin-off of \"\"The Practice\"\", followed the exploits of attorneys at Crane, Poole & Schmidt?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the title of the most famous painting by Franz Hals?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nPedro Lascurin had the shortest Presidency of less than one hour (sources quote ranges between 15 and 55 minutes), of which country, thus giving it three presidents in one day on 18 February 1913?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCharles Sands (USA), Margaret Abbot (USA) and George Lyon (Canada) were winners in what Olympic sport at the 1900 and 1904 games?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho according to legend was the son of Zeus and Europa and became King of Crete?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho played Inspector Clouseau in the films made from 1963 to 1978?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name is given to a positive whole number that can only be divided by 1 or itself?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat do the letters GF mean on a menu?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The three actors who played guitar in the band in the film \"\"Spinal Tap\"\" got together again as a folk trio \"\"The Folksmen\"\" in which film?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJohn Calvin, 16th century French theologian, was the autocrat of which city for 13 years, where he improved the city and provided harsh punishments for moral transgressions?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Founded in London in 1766, what activity are \"\"Christie, Manson and Woods\"\" involved in?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat building, erected at Sydenham near London in 1834 in 200 acres of grounds and given to the public in 1920, was gutted by fire in 1936?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which Welsh poet (e.g. \"\"Portrait of the Artist as a Young Dog\"\") wrote a play \"\"Under Milk Wood\"\" that was published posthumously in 1954?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho, on his 72nd birthday in 1951, was not persuaded by UPI photographer Arthur Sassehim to smile, but stuck out his tongue instead?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What was the first pop video directed by John Landis, whose directing credits include \"\"National Lampoon's Animal House\"\" and \"\"The Blues Brothers\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich British comedy-drama series (1979 to 1994) starred George Cole as Arthur Daley, an unscrupulous importer-exporter, wholesaler, and used-car salesman and Dennis Waterman as Terry McCann, his bodyguard?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nPrince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh, was born on which island?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich American football quarterback is the only player to win the AP Most Valuable Player three consecutive times (199597) and holds NFL records including most passing yards (65,127), most pass completions (5,720), and most career victories as a starting quarterback (169)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nExcluding Antarctica, which continent reaches the furthest south?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the next in this series: St. Devote, Massenet, Casino Square , Mirabeau, Loews ... ?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The Tiergarten, German for \"\"Animal Garden\"\", is the name of both a park and a locality in which city?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Larry Levine, an American audio engineer, who won a Grammy Award in 1966 for \"\"A Taste of Honey\"\" by Herb Alpert & the Tijuana Brass and contributed to The Beach Boys' 1966 album \"\"Pet Sounds\"\", was best known for his co-operation on the Wall of Sound recording technique with which producer?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is a domesticated animal that resembles a small llama in superficial appearance that are kept in herds that graze on the level heights of the Andes of South America at an altitude of 3,500 m (11,483 ft) to 5,000 m (16,404 ft) above sea-level, that were bred specifically for the fibre in their fleece?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Whose first album was called \"\"Voice of an Angel\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho did the British fight at the Battle of Rorke's Drift in 1879?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the leader of the Peasant's Revolt in 1381 who, after killing a poll tax collector, marched on London with supporters and was killed there at Smithfield by the Lord Mayor of London?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 2006 Grammy Award for the Best Musical Theatre recording were John Du Prez & Eric Idle (producers & composers) and Eric Idle (lyricist) for which show?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho discovered the two moons of Mars in 1877?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat activity became legal in The Republic of Ireland when the 15th Amendment to the Constitution was passed in 1995?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which country is the port of Incheon?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What song is this lyric from: \"\"Driver at the engine, fireman rings the bell, sandman swings the lantern to show that all is well\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere is the world's widest street?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAustralian Shane Warne is associated with which sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which sport did Olympic gold medallists Roger Ducret, Lucien Gaudin, Laura Flessel-Colovic, Gaston Alibert, Pascale Trinquet, Christian d'Oriola, Jehan Buhan and Albert Robert Ayat represent France?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat type of book are accounts usually written in?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the first name of \"\"Seinfeld\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAfter watching US president Barack Obama giving a speech, David Letterman commented that it was nice to have a president who could pronounce which word?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the thick watery substance filling the space between the lens and the retina of the eye?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat film production company was named after brothers Harry (born Hirsz), Albert (born Aaron), Sam (born Szmul), and Jack (born Itzhak)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWith which sport is O J Simpson associated?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the name of the principle that \"\"if two explanations account equally well for a particular phenomenon, the one to be chosen is the one with the fewer assumptions\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name used in North America for a man who makes his living by felling trees?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich American science fiction television series, first aired from 1993 to 2002, tapped into public mistrust of governments and large institutions and interest in conspiracy theories and spirituality, centring on efforts to uncover the existence of extraterrestrial life?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOn 15 February 1990 the United Kingdom restored diplomatic relations after 8 years, with which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who is a South African serial killer who committed the \"\"ABC Murders\"\" between 1994 and 1995, with over 30 victims?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nGenerals Gallieni, Manoury, Joffre, French, von Kluck, von Blow and von Moltke were involved in which battle that stopped the German advance in 1914 during World War I?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who won a gold medal at the 1976 Summer Olympics, married Kris Kardashian in 1991 and from 2007 starred in the E! reality series \"\"Keeping Up with the Kardashians\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich detective was created by G K Chesterton?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich wonder of the ancient world was at Ephesus?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of a shoe that is traditionally made of wood?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is a popular name for the North American bison?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What entertainment venue in New York City's Rockefeller Center, nicknamed \"\"the Showplace of the Nation\"\", opened to the public in December 1932?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAcccording to the English nursey rhyme, what did little Jack Horner pull out of a pie?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBadminton debuted at the 1992 Summer Olympics. How many different people have won gold medals for the men's singles event in its first 5 Olympiads to 2008?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name was given to a series of thirty evening radio speeches given by US President Franklin D. Roosevelt in 1933 and 1944?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe final carrier of the Olympic flame in the Olympic Torch Relay is often kept secret until the last moment, and is usually who?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere is the Sea of Vapors?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1403, Venice imposed a waiting period for those wishing to enter the city, to see if they would develop the plague. How long was this period of isolation?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1487, Portuguese navigator Bartholomew Diaz was the first European to sail past which landmark?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere was the siege of the Alamo?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the first name of de Gaulle, the first President of French Fifth Republic from 1959 to 1969?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCanberra is the capital of which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Battle of Ghuznee in 1839 took place between the armies of Great Britain and which other country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe names for the satellites of which planet are chosen from characters from the works of William Shakespeare and Alexander Pope?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nTypically, a male moose sheds its antlers how frequently?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIf someone has a BA, they are a Bachelor of what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who was the fourth (and the first female) Prime Minister of the State of Israel, who was described as the \"\"Iron Lady\"\" (before Margaret Thatcher), \"\"the best man in the government\"\" and the \"\"strong-willed, straight-talking, grey-bunned grandmother of the Jewish people\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA novel by General Lew Wallace published in 1880 was made into which films in 1926 (a silent movie) and 1959 (produced by William Wyler)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which Italian nobel prize winner (1934) wrote novels such as \"\"Mal Gioconda\"\" and switched to writing plays in 1910?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the common name for Hydrocephalus, a pathological condition whereby fluid is retained within the skull?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who wrote numerous short stories and plays and the novels \"\"Of Human Bondage\"\", \"\"The Moon And Sixpence\"\" and \"\"Cakes And Ale\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Dr. Benjamin Spock, the American pediatrician who wrote \"\"Baby and Child Care\"\", published in 1946, won an Olympic gold medal in what type of event?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What musical has the characters Roxie Hart, Velma Kelly, Billy Flynn, Matron \"\"Mama\"\" Morton, Amos Hart, Mary Sunshine, Fred Casely, Mrs. Borusewicz, Harrison and Go-to-Hell Kitty Baxter?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name for an argument presented in logical form, containing 2 premises and a conclusion?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the James Bond film \"\"The World Is Not Enough\"\" who played Bond girl Elektra King?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMeasuring from the closest point of each of these countries to the equator, which is the furthest from the equator?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is a form of word play that deliberately exploits ambiguity between similar-sounding words for humorous or rhetorical effect?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCathay is a poetic name for which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"\"\"Yabba dabba doo\"\" was a catch-phrase in which cartoon series?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAccording to legend, who was King Arthur's father?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was first demonstrated by Alexander Graham Bell at the Philadelphia Exhibition in 1876?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat international organisation was created in 1958 to bring about economic integration between European nations?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat fictional Chinese-American detective, created by Earl Derr Biggers in 1923 for a novel published in 1925, was the subject of over 45 films made between 1926 and 1981?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nQuantrill's Raiders, a loosely organised force of Partisan rangers under the leadership of William Clarke Quantril, fought in which war?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the original surname of T E Shaw, an RAF aircraftsman who was killed in a motorbike accident in 1935?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n111,111,111 squared gives what result?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe peacock belongs to which family of birds?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the TV series \"\"Thunderbirds\"\", Parker was chauffeur to whom?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nFor a proper fraction, the numerator is\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the least number of shots that a competitor can take to complete 18 holes of golf?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The names of how many states of the USA start and end with the letter \"\"a\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCanadian Florence Nightingale Graham dropped out of nursing school in Toronto and joined her elder brother in New York City, working as a bookkeeper for the E.R. Squibb Pharmaceuticals Company. By what name is she better known?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn weaving, what are the threads running parallel to the length of the cloth called?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat passes between the sun and earth to make a solar eclipse?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Treaty of Fontainebleau, signed on 11 April 1814 by representatives of France, Austria, Hungary, Bohemia, Russia, and Prussia, had a marked effect on the personal life of whom?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhen is Labour Day in the USA, Bermuda and Canada?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat Australian weekly magazine founded by two Sydney journalists, J.F. Archibald and John Haynes, which first appeared on 31 January 1880, ceased publication on 23 January 2008?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMallard, Mandarin, Red-crested Pochard, Teal, Muscovy and Eider are all types of what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What are the words called in crosswords that appear under the headings \"\"Across\"\" and \"\"Down\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the original British series of \"\"Who Wants To Be A Millionaire\"\", question 8 was worth what amount?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the first Pope to be appointed in the 21st century?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nHow many books in the Bible's Old Testament are included in the Catholic version but not in the Protestant one?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA particular song was copyrighted in 1935 by the Summy Company, crediting authors Preston Ware Orem and Mrs. R.R. Forman. The company was purchased in 1990 by Warner Chappell for US$15 million, with the value of the song estimated at US$5 million. What is the song?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat style of American Football founded in 2003 is a full-contact 7 a side game where uniforms consist of helmets, shoulder pads, elbow pads, knee pads, bras, and panties?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIf you travelled down the Missouri River from Bismarck, North Dakota, which city would you be in when you reached the ocean?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In David Hockney's painting \"\"Mr and Mrs Clark and Percy\"\", what is Percy?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho won the 2010 Boston Marathon with a time of 2:05:52, easily breaking the course record of 2:07:14?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who, an influential English occultist and ceremonial magician, known today for his magical writings, was a hedonist, bisexual, recreational drug experimenter and social critic, and was called in the popular press of the day \"\"the wickedest man in the world\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich 1974 film about a train hijacking starring Walter Matthau and Robert Shaw was remade in 2009 starring John Travolta and Denzel Washington?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the setting for the Alfred Hitchcock film \"\"The Birds\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat satellite, launched by NASA aboard a Delta rocket from Cape Canaveral on 10 July 1962, was built as part of a multi-national agreement between AT&T;, Bell Telephone Laboratories, NASA, the British General Post Office, and the French National PTT (Post, Telegraph & Telecom Office)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAfter sporadic visits by European explorers and merchants from the 17th century onwards, the eastern half of which continent was claimed by the British in 1770, and officially settled as a penal colony on 26 January 1788?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name is given to art that depicts inanimate (typically commonplace) objects, either natural (e.g. food, flowers, plants, rocks & shells) or man-made (e.g. drinking glasses, books, vases, jewelry, coins & pipes) in an artificial setting?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the tallest skyscraper in Saudi Arabia, one of the world's 50th tallest buildings, that is in Riyadh?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho, the illegitimate son of a peasant girl, was educated in the studio of a Florentine painter, spent much of his early working life in the service of Ludovico il Moro in Milan, worked in Rome, Bologna and Venice, and spent his final years in France at the home given to him by King Franois I?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere was there a series of explosions and fire on 23 October 1989 (killing 23 employees and injuring 314), an explosion on 23 June 1999 (killing two men and injuring three) and an explosion and fire on 27 March 2000 (which caused 1 death and 71 injuries)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name for the act of murdering of one's own sister?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which country is the city of Maastricht?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich team has played in 40 of the 105 Baseball World Series and won 27 World Series championships (between 1923 and 2009), the most of any Major League franchise?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The \"\"Hall of Mirrors\"\" is in which building?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is another name for the alligator pear?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho presented a list of 23 problems in mathematics at a conference of the International Congress of Mathematicians on 8 August 1900 in the Sorbonne, of which only 10 have resolutions which are fully accepted?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho lived in the Lateran Palace from the fourth to the fourteenth centuries?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What type of sentence is \"\"pack my red box with five dozen quality jugs\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What was the mission of \"\"Earthview 01: The Founders Flight\"\" which was launched on 21 April 1997?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nLee Kuan Yew and Goh Chok Tong were the first two Prime Ministers of which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The song \"\"Love To Love You Baby\"\" was banned by the BBC in 1975. Who was the artist?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat French military unit was established in 1831 to enable people from other countries to serve in the French Armed Forces, commanded by French officers?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAs at 2010, which team had played the most seasons of professional baseball games without winning the World Series, with their last win in 1908?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich river runs through the cities of Basel, Strasbourg, Karlsruhe, Mainz, Koblenz, Bonn, Cologne, Dsseldorf, Arnhem, Utrecht and Rotterdam?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho won his third rowing Olympic gold medal with Steve Redgrave in 2000?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"A novel by Edgar Rice Burroughs, first published in \"\"All-Story Magazine\"\" in October 1912, was \"\"Tarzan of the ... \"\" what?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nHow many black keys are there on a standard modern piano?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which sport did Andre Agassi's father Mike Agassi compete in the 1948 and 1952 Olympics, represented Iran?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the first name of the painter Manet?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is a name for a type of private club in city outskirts or rural areas that usually offers a variety of recreational sports facilities such as golf, tennis, swimming and polo?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the national government body for scientific research in Australia that was founded in 1926 as the \"\"Advisory Council of Science and Industry\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat genus of flowering plants, native to an area from Brazil to Peru to southern Argentina discovered in 1768 by French botanist Philibert Commeron, is a thorny, woody vine reaching from 1 to 12 metres tall by growing over other plants with hooked thorns tipped with a black, waxy substance?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nFarthings were in use in England as coinage from the 13th century and ceased to be legal tender on 31 December 1960. How many of them were there in a pound (1)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the largest passenger ship by gross tonnage when she took her maiden voyage on 4 June 2006?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich horse race is held at Churchill Downs?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nGeoff Capes, twice the world's strongest man, won 2 Olympic Games gold medals in which sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn Greek mythology, who were the band of heroes who accompanied Jason to Colchis in his quest to find the Golden Fleece?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOf the 26 times that the 100 metres has been included in the Olympic Games to 2008, which country has won the most gold medals (16)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat paraffin-derived clear, transparent liquid developed in 1924 by W. J. Stoddard and Lloyd E. Jackson began to be used by dry cleaners in 1928 and has become a common organic solvent used in painting and decorating?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Someone who deprives themselves of sleep is said to be \"\"burning the ... what ... at both ends\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which organisation runs the undergraduate college in Annapolis, Maryland, USA, that is known as \"\"The Academy\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nSherlock Holmes was proficient in which fictional martial art invented by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the Mississippi State Penitentiary formerly called?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The \"\"phylloxera epidemic\"\" affects what?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"\"\"Give me Liberty, or give me Death!\"\" is a quotation attributed to which speaker at a court hearing on 23 March 1775, at St. John's Church in Richmond, Virginia?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich musical term denotes slurred staccato, notated by adding a slur to staccato notes, and is played almost legato, with each note 'carried' to the next?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe initial parts of which London building were built as a fortress by the Normans, had additions to become a palace and then was used primarily as a prison?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name is given to the syndrome which involves a delusion that the affected person can transform or has transformed into an animal?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Until 2004, when the International Judging System (IJS) (informally called the \"\"Code of Points\"\") was introduced, what was the highest score a judge could award in figure skating for each of the \"\"free skate\"\" and the \"\"short\"\" programmes?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name was given to the English Civil war in the 15th century between the rival houses of Lancaster and York?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Where would one find \"\"Bachmann's bundle\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe island called Martha's Vineyard off the south of Cape Cod in New England is in which state of the USA?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1848, Mexico ratified the Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo, officially ceding what to the USA?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho famously gatecrashed a state dinner for Indian President Manmohan Singh at the White House on 24 November 2009?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich city, since the 14th century BC, has been controlled by Israelites, Judaeans, Babylonians, Persians, Greeks, Hasmoneans, Romans, Byzantines, Arabs, Mamluks, Turks, and the British and for a short time after World War II was occupied by Israel and Jordan?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe island of Taiwan is off the coast of where?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the tool used to sharpen a knife?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat sign of the zodiac is represented by a lion?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"How many people made up the English pop rock group \"\"Tears For Fears\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere was the first competition named the FIFA Club World Cup held in 2006?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the word for the process of using strong acid or mordant to cut into the unprotected parts of a metal surface to create a design in intaglio in the metal?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat part of the world has been ruled by Aelle, Ceawlin, Ethelberht, Rdwald, Edwin, Oswald, Oswy, Wulfhere, Ethelred, Ethelbald, Offa, Cnwulf and Egbert?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nProject SCORE, the worlds first communications satellite, was launched when?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the only country in the southern hemisphere to have won a gold medal in the Winter Olympics?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Great Sphinx of Giza in Egypt is a statue of a reclining mythical creature with a lion's body and the head of a what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who painted \"\"Boy With a Pipe\"\" which, in May 2004, was sold for a record price of $104 million?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn October 2010, who sued Steve McQueen's fashion company, Alexander McQueen, and retail giant Saks, for trademark infringement?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name for a piece of exercise equipment consisting of a metal bar, one or more sets of weight plates, and a set of collars?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Ironman World Championship, which has been held annually in Hawaii since 1978, with an additional race in 1982, involves which sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is a \"\"white dwarf\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the James Bond film \"\"Goldfinger\"\" who played Bond girl Pussy Galore?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the fictional family with children called Greg, Peter, Bobby, Marcia, Jan and Cindy, that first came to US TV screens in 1969?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the line separating the numerator and denominator of a fraction if it is written as a diagonal line?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nSet up in 1954 as a merger of smaller groups, the Front de Libration Nationale fought a war for independence from France until 1962, when the French government signed a cease-fire agreement. The FLN became the only legal party in which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was ousted as Panama's leader after a 1989 US invasion ordered by President George H.W. Bush, was convicted of drug racketeering and related charges in 1992, and was extradited to France at the end of April 2010 on charges of laundering around US$3 million in drug proceeds by buying luxury apartments in Paris?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat character created by Robert Ludlum appeared in a film trilogy released between 2002 to 2007?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the disease that Stephen Hawking has?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe rings of which planet were first detected in 1980 but only identified in 1989 by the Voyager 2 spacecraft? .\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nFormula 1 driver Ayrton Senna died while leading the 1994 San Marino Grand Prix at which motor racing circuit?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which novel does Michael Henchard sell his wife and child for 5 guineas?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which tree produces red fruits called \"\"haws\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe capital of Brazil was moved from Rio de Janeiro to the purpose-built capital city of Brasilia in what year?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Rio Grande forms the border of Texas with what other area?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Indonesian Army special forces group, founded in 1952, that conducts special operations missions for the Indonesian government is called what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIvan the Terrible was a czar of what country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What was the code-name for the reporters Bernstein and Woodward's contact during their investigation of the \"\"Watergate\"\" scandal?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1947, Chuck Yeager was the first to do what in an aeroplane?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat compete at the Burghley Trials, Badminton, the Rolex Kentucky Three Day, the Adelaide Trials, the Luhmhlen Trials and the toiles de Pau?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1968, what telephone number was established as the national emergency number for the United States?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the word for the projection on a ship that holds a lifeboat?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJune Middleton, of Melbourne, Australia, who died aged 83 in 2009, was in the Guinness Book of Records for spending the most time in what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the nursery rhyme beginning \"\"Hey Diddle Diddle\"\", who ran away with the spoon?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere was the first annual G6 leaders summit (which later became the G8) held in 1975?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 2003, what character was voted by the American Film Institute to be the greatest hero in American film?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho won the gold medal for the 100m at the 1992 Olympics at 32 years of age and became the oldest Olympic 100 m champion by four years?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the system of stellar designation in which a specific star is identified by a Greek letter (then Latin letters in lower-case then upper-case), followed by the genitive form of its parent constellation's Latin name (e.g. Tauri)?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which decade was Barack Obama born?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Whose autobiography \"\"Going Rogue\"\" was published in 2009?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of a bishop's staff that is shaped like a shepherd's crook?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCricketer W G Grace, who played first-class cricket from 1865 to 1908, also captained England from 1903 to 1908 in what other sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was king of the Anglo-Saxon kingdom of Wessex from 871 to 899, notable for his defence of the Anglo-Saxon kingdoms of southern England against the Vikings, and for improving his kingdom's legal system and military structure?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the 16th century, which explorer began and led the first known successful circumnavigation of the earth?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho designed the British World War II fighter plane, the Spitfire?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the films \"\"Batman Forever\"\" (1995) and \"\"Batman & Robin\"\" (1997) who was Bruce Wayne's ward?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat TV character worked as a salesman at Gary's Shoes in Chicago, Illinois?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe music of which band finally became available for download from iTunes in November 2010?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho invaded Europe from Mongolia and Turkey over 300 years, beginning in the 13th century?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Grand Old Party or GOP is the name for which political party in the USA?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat country is the world's largest producer of Tobacco?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who was the goalkeeper for England's opening match in the 2010 FIFA World Cup against the USA on 12 June, whose performance made headlines in the UK such as \"\"The Hand of Clod\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who says \"\"Is this a dagger that I see before me\"\" in a Shakespearean play?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nPrince Charles founded what organisation in 1976 to help young employed people?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhose armies were defeated at the Battle of Waterloo in 1815?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"How many gifts are there in the \"\"Twelve Days of Christmas\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich river is most sacred to the Hindu religion?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMost of the world's caviar comes from where?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the first female artist to have a #1 album in the USA and the UK simultaneously?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which Canadian, born Eilleen Regina Edwards, made the album \"\"Come on Over\"\", the best-selling album of all time by a female musician and the best-selling album in the history of country music?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of Madonna's proposed chain of fitness clubs?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was elected Governor of the US State of Texas in 1994?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich country produces the most of the world's olive oil?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich island is famous for its carved stone statues?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn November 2010, Genoveva Aonma and sisters Bilguissa Simpor and Salimata Simpor of which national women's soccer team were accused by newspapers in Nigeria and Cameroon of being men, not women?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBeatrice Tinsley was well known in what field?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich company was founded by Bill Gates and Paul Allen in Albuquerque, New Mexico, on 4 April 1975 to develop and sell BASIC interpreters for a new microcomputer, the Altair 8800?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat US public holiday falls on the 3rd Monday in February every year?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nGoliath is the name for a South American spider that eats what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"A 1993 film starring Tom Hanks was \"\"Sleepless in ... \"\" where?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich expression is associated with the sinking of the HMS Birkenhead at Gansbaai near Cape Town, South Africa, in Febuary 1852?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The song \"\"Love is All Around\"\" by Wet Wet Wet featured on the soundtrack for which 1994 film?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is another name for \"\"mother of pearl\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the 1930s, who was the first to win all 4 tennis Grand Slam titles?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the substance that causes irritation from a sting by a nettle or an ant?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJohn Lennon's hand-written lyrics for which song sold for US$1.2 million at Sotheby's in June 2010?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What sport is featured in \"\"Invictus\"\", a 2009 film directed by Clint Eastwood?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is a group of jellyfish called?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat item of headwear is associated with Sherlock Holmes?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich shipping passage was closed from 1967 to 1975?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Sheep are aged by their teeth and are referred to by the number of permanent incisors that have erupted. About how old is an \"\"eight-tooth\"\" or full-mouth sheep, which is also referred to as 'aged'?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the first female prime minister of the Republic of India, who served for three consecutive terms from 1966 to 1977 and then from 1980 until her assassination in 1984?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What profession had been followed by Yorick, a character in Shakespeare's \"\"Hamlet\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the longest time that there can be between General Elections in the UK?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The narrative poem \"\"The Gypsies\"\" (1824) by Alexander Pushkin influenced a novella by Prosper Mrime (1845), which was the basis for a libretto by Henri Meilhac and Ludovic Halvy for which opera that premiered at the Opra-Comique of Paris in 1875?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In Victorian England, what was a \"\"reticule\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCeladon is a shade of what colour?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Battle of Balaclava was in which war?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the art form where objects are glued to, usually, a piece of paper or canvas?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"From which language do we get the word \"\"dungarees\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the nickname of tennis player Mark Philippoussis?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is identified by an I. S. B. N.?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which album by Lily Allen contained the tracks \"\"The Fear\"\", \"\"Not Fair\"\" and \"\"22\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"How many adjectives are there in the sentence \"\"Jack ran down the path.\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the books by the Rev. W. V. Awdry and the UK TV series first broadcast in 1984 with Ringo Starr as storyteller, how many wheels does Thomas the Tank Engine have?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat word means to sell scarce shares or tickets at a quick profit?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the literal translation of the name Las Vegas?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"An \"\"ISBN\"\" is an identification number found on what item?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nPlayers form scrums in which sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What word refers to the period before \"\"The Great Flood\"\" as described in the Old Testament of the Bible?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat relation were Ravi Shankar and Norah Jones to each other?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJohn Sholto Douglas sponsored the rules for which sport in the 19th century?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe islands of Malta, Sardinia, Sicily and Corsica are in which Sea?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat were Scotsmen prohibited from wearing 1746-1782 under the Highland Garb Act, after the rising in Scotland in 1745?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Limpopo River separates Zimbabwe and Botswana from what country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the 19th century, the term \"\"penny dreadful\"\" applied to what item?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich American bluegrass-country singer and fiddler has won 26 Grammy Awards, making her the most awarded female artist (and the third most awarded artist overall) in Grammy history since she recorded for the first time at the age of 14?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the short bar with weights at each end that is sometimes used by bodybuilders?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWith what group are Bobby Seale and Huey P. Newton associated?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The \"\"Three Laws of Motion\"\" are named after which scientist who published them in 1687?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Where was the sport called \"\"Tossing the caber\"\" developed?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which city can you visit the Luigi Ferraris Stadium, the gardens of the Villa Durazzo-Pallavicini, the Piazza De Ferrari, the cemetery of Staglieno, the Edoardo Chiossone Museum of Oriental Art and the Torre della Lanterna?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the first US president to succeed to the Presidency upon the assassination of his predecessor and the first US President to be impeached?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which American vocalist (described by the British newspaper \"\"The Guardian\"\" as \"\"one of the greatest voices of her generation\"\") whose repertoire included jazz, blues, folk, gospel and pop, was unknown outside Washington, D.C., until after she died of melanoma in 1996?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAdmiral Sir John Jellicoe commanded the British fleet at the Battle of Jutland, the largest naval battle of World War I, against a fleet from which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The \"\"Giant Marbles\"\" rock formation in the USA is in which national park?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the real name of \"\"Baby Spice\"\" of the Spice Girls, whose 2007 single \"\"All I Need to Know\"\" was the lowest-charting single of her solo career?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In the United Kingdom, what is \"\"The Solent\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What profession requires the artist to know about \"\"F stops\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In which song does the singer sing about \"\"the way you wear your hat, the way you sip your tea\"\", and \"\"the way you hold your knife, the way we danced till three\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJudith Keppel was the first winner of the top prize on which UK programme?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the minimum number of points needed to win a tiebreak in tennis, such as in the Hopman Cup for mixed doubles, on the ATP and WTA tours for doubles and sometmes in USTA league play?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The song \"\"Good Morning To All\"\", composed by Pattie and Mildred Hill in 1893, is now sung as what?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhen are the events surrounding the legend of the Pied Piper of Hamelin supposed to have taken place?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1973 the Paris Peace Accords were held in an attempt to end which war?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat Brazilian city exports more coffee than any other port in the world?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which country were 29 miners killed after 2 explosions in the Pike River Mine in November 2010, making it the most-deadly mining disaster there in 96 years?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Misses World for both 1999 and 2000 represented which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In 2006 English politician George Galloway was widely quoted as saying that it would be \"\"morally justified if someone chose to assassinate \"\" whom?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat name is given to describes the phenomenon of the gradual mixing of two different substances which are in contact?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCenter, Offensive guard, Offensive tackle, Tight end, Wide receiver, Fullback, Running back, Quarterback, Defensive end, Defensive tackle, Nose guard, Linebacker, Cornerback, Safety, Nickelback and Dimeback are positions in which sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAmerican rapper Tramar Dillard is better known by what stage name?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAlan Bates played an escaped convict who was mistaken for the son of God in which 1961 film?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the name given to the largest alluvial gold nugget discovered by John Deason and Richard Oates at Moliagul, Victoria, Australia on 5 February 1869?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the current name of the islands originally called the \"\"Sandwich Islands\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat began when Bohemia revolted against the Habsburgs in 1618?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 2006, who became the second basketball player to score over 80 points in an NBA game?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhose birth and death are commemorated on the same day?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What sport has been contested annually in Britain since 1715 in the race called \"\"Doggett's Coat and Badge\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMaine Coon, Munchkin, Oriental Shorthair, Persian, Ragamuffin, Russian Blue, Siamese, Siberian, Snowshoe, Sphynx, Tonkinese and Manx are all breeds of what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn Germany, what is an autobahn?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich 2008 Western film starred Ed Harris and Viggo Mortensen as lawmen, Jeremy Irons as a rancher and Renee Zellweger as a piano-playing widow?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat are muslin and chenille?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What organisation was founded in 1831 by James Winston, Samuel James Arnold, Samuel Beazley, Sir Andrew Francis Barnard, and Francis Mills to \"\"tend to the regeneration of the Drama\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1995, Steffi Graf became the only tennis player to have won each of the four grand slam events how many times?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nActor Omar Sharif is one of the world's leading players of which game?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the favourite drink of a vampire?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich Frenchman, who never learned to speak Swedish, became King Charles XIV John of Sweden and Norway?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat type of building is likely to have a minaret?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which year was the first robbery for which it is known that Jesse James was responsible, of the Davies's County Savings Association in Gallatin, Missouri, during which Jesse shot and killed the cashier, Captain John Sheets?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"On 2 November 2010, the oil painting \"\"Nude Sitting on a Divan\"\" sold for $68.9 million, a record for an artwork by which artist?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"A \"\"land run\"\" into which current state of the USA began at noon on 22 April 1889, when an estimated 50,000 people lined up to race to claim 160 acre (0.65 km2) pieces of the available 2 million acres (8,000 km)?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which country set up the \"\"Committee on Public Information\"\" from April 1917 to June 1919 to run a propaganda campaign using newsprint, posters, radio, telegraph, cable and movies to broadcast its message, including fabrications (e.g. images of enemy soldiers killing babies and hoisting them on bayonets), and told citizens to seek out spies, which led to the creation of \"\"patriotic organizations,\"\" which spied, tapped telephones, and opened mail in an effort to ferret out \"\"spies and traitors\"\" (i.e. anyone who called for peace, questioned the war's progress, or criticized government policies)?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat should you cross for good luck?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 2006 Monty Panesar became the first person of what religion to play test cricket for England?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat are the tetrahedron, cube, octahedron, dodecahedron and icosahedron known as?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat separates Wales from Devon, England?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBenot B. Mandelbrot worked on a wide range of mathematical problems, including mathematical physics and quantitative finance, but is best known as the father of what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe island of Tasmania is governed by which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Black Hawk War was for possession of lands east of the Mississippi. In which modern day state was the first confrontation, at Stillman's Run, on 14 May 1832, which resulted in a victory for Chief Black Hawk's Sauk and Fox warriors over the local militiamen commanded by Major Isaiah Stillman?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"How is the title of Rossini's opera \"\"La Gazza Ladra\"\" usually translated into English?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nHoratio was a legendary Roman hero who defended a bridge against which army?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 2010, what North American horse broke the All-time North American female earnings record with over $6 million, broke two world records for Grade/Group I (for consecutive victories and the All-time North American record number of victories by a filly/mare), and tied the All-time North American record for the number of consecutive victories without defeat?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich event held in Alberta, Canada, which bills itself as The Greatest Outdoor Show on Earth, is a large festival, exhibition, and rodeo held for 10 days every summer in July, attracts more than 1.2 million visitors?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Sagrada Famlia in Barcelona, which began construction in 1882, was consecrated and declared a basilica by the Pope in what year?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the only county in the USA to border 5 counties from 5 different states : Baca County, Colorado; Morton 