onse:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What Latin phrase means means to speak under one's breath, literally \"\"under voice\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat natural effect is only visible during a total eclipse of the sun?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nStirling who was a British racing driver, who raced from 1948 to 1962 and won 212 of the 529 races he entered, including 16 Formula One Grands Prix?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Nobel Peace Prize winner for 2010 lives in which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who wrote the music for the musical \"\"A Chorus Line\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich English town is known for its collection of concrete cows?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nLieutenant General James Thomas Brudenell, who commanded the Light Brigade of the British Army during the Crimean War, was the 7th Earl of what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nHow many US states border Lake Superior?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the last Anglo-Saxon king of England?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere was the world's tallest road bridge opened in December 2004?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was named after American frontiersman James Bowie?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat team does controversial quarterback Michael Vick play for in the National Football League in the USA?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nElvis Presley sang a few lines in German on which US hit song?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Charlie Sheen starred as which character in the TV series \"\"Two and a Half Men\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who published \"\"A Book of Nonsense\"\" (a volume of limericks that went through three editions) in 1846, \"\"The History of the Seven Families of the Lake Pipple-Popple\"\" in 1865, and \"\"The Owl and the Pussycat\"\" in 1867?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho performed in t