t wood with an attractive grain?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nFrom 1937 to 1942 Alan Lomax, who contributed more than 10,000 field recordings of folk music from the USA, the Caribbean, Ireland, Great Britain, Spain, and Italy, was Assistant in Charge of the Archive of Folk Song of what establishment?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which composer wrote \"\"Night and Day\"\", \"\"I Get a Kick out of You\"\", \"\"Well, Did You Evah!\"\" and \"\"I've Got You Under My Skin\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nLloyd's of London, a British insurance and reinsurance market, began around 1688 in what kind of place?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAntananarivo is the capital of which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Dido was \"\"featured\"\" on the song \"\"Sam\"\", which was written and performed by whom?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the maximum number of points that can be scored from a single shot in basketball?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who wrote the poem \"\"Daffodils\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat are the topmost 7 vertebrae of the backbone called?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the 18th century, the capital of Russia was moved from Moscow to where?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe language known as Putonghua, Guoyu, Gwok Yu and Huayu, is spoken in Taiwan, Malaysia and Singapore and where else that it is the official language?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nDamascus is the capital of which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which \"\"Bond girl\"\" met Ringo Starr when they starred in the 1981 film \"\"Caveman\"\", and later married him?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich English cricket captain had a well-publicised row with Pakistani umpire Shakoor Rana in Faisalabad in 1987?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The score for the Broadway musical \"\"Kismet\"\" was adapted from the music of