reds of adults and children?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nGeorge Cukor directed which 1964 film musical?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the name of the feast day in the Western Christian calendar which occurs on 29 September to honour the defeat of Lucifer in the battle for the heavens, for which the traditional meal includes goose (a \"\"stubble-goose\"\", i.e. one prepared around harvest time)?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nLenny Bruce was in what field of entertainment in the 1960s?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which country were democratic elections held in May 1989, and though Guillermo Endara was elected president, the results were annulled by the existing government?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich is the film, about canine reincarnation and the relationships between father and son and master and dog, based on an Alan Sharp adaptation of a short novel by Irish author Lord Dunsany?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat are Jimmy Reed, Skip James, Elmore James & Big Bill Broonzy best known as?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat ancient civilization was centred in the north of ancient Canaan, with its heartland along the coastal regions of modern day Lebanon, Syria and Israel?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere was the first permanent European settlement established in North America?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the medical description of the loss of hair from the head or body, sometimes to the extent of baldness?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Treaty of Kiel, between the UK, Sweden and Denmark-Norway was intended to ease hostilities relating to which war?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOn 31 May 2010, the President of which country announced his resignation after local politicians criticised comments he made in relation to overseas military deployments?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho became the first king of the