ion:\nWhat is the name for a hare's nest?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho hosted the 2006 Academy Awards ceremony?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who played Vyvyan, a psychotic punk metal medical student with orange-dyed & spiked hair and four metal stars embedded in his forehead, in the UK TV series \"\"The Young Ones\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The song \"\"I Could Be So Good For You\"\" was from which British TV series?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat post was held by Winston Churchill during the 1926 General Strike in the UK?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who had a hit record in 1990 with \"\"U Can't Touch This\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nTo what office in the USA was Henry Kissinger appointed in 1973?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"According to a 2009 adventure family film starring Ashley Tisdale, Carter Jenkins, Robert Hoffman, Henri Young, Regan Young and Austin Butler, \"\"The aliens are\"\" where?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhere, in 2011 and since, is a major gathering place in Egypt for expressing protest?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat does a querulous person do?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOn the buttons of a VCR or DVD player, what does the sign in the shape of a square mean?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBy what name is James Osterberg popularly known?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWith what is FIFA usually associated?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat links the US, 2 May 2011 and Abottabad in Pakistan?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMichael Phelps who during the Summer Olympics 2012 brought his swimming medal total to a record 18 golds represents which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat substance, best known as a poison, was used in small doses in medications as a stimulant, as a laxative, and for enhancing performance in sports?\n\n### Response:\n", "#